com.camerontec.util.datamodel

Class NullField

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.datamodel.NullField
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Encodable, Field, FieldValue, IntKeyed, Nullable, OrderedCollection<FieldGroup>, OrderedCollectionOfFieldGroups, Recyclable

    public final class NullField
extends Object
implements Field
    A distinguished FieldGroup variant for indicating a field group with key or value or nested groups.

    This field:

    • Is a singleton (see INSTANCE) and may not be cloned
    • Is immutable
    • Has no associated FieldValue
    • Contains no field groups
    • Is equal only with itself

        public Field setMutableString(MutableString value)
        Description copied from interface: FieldValue
        Set the field value as a MutableString.

        Note that, as for other types, this method transfers ownership of the specified value to the Field object. It is more important in this case, however, because of its mutability. That is, if the value is modified after this call then so is the Field object to which ownership was transferred.
